@{
  ViewData["Title"] = "Projects | Clint McMahon";
}
<section class="projects py-5">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Projects</h2>
    <div class="row mb-5">
      <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto text-center">
        <p class="lead">A collection of side projects born from curiosity, creativity, and the drive to build something useful.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-10 mx-auto">
        
        <div class="row align-items-center mb-4 pb-4">
          <div class="col-md-2 mb-3 mb-md-0">
            <a href="https://nyccoffeemap.com">
              <img src="/images/2026/nyc_coffee_icon.png" alt="NYC Coffee Map" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm" style="max-width: 150px;" />
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-10">
            <h4>NYC Coffee Map</h4>
            <p>A React Native app for finding specialty coffee shops across New York City. Independent roasters, espresso bars and third-wave cafes with chains filtered out so the noise is already gone before you open the map. It uses live Google Places data and AI-generated summaries to give a real sense of each shop before committing to the subway ride.</p>
            <p>The app includes an NYC-specific subway overlay that renders live transit lines and stops directly on the map making it easy to find a great cup that's actually on your route. Built on the same codebase as the Minnesota and Chicago variants with the subway layer as a feature unique to New York.</p>
            <a href="https://nyccoffeemap.com" class="btn btn-outline-primary">View Project →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr class="my-4" />

        <div class="row align-items-center mb-4 pb-4">
          <div class="col-md-2 mb-3 mb-md-0">
            <a href="https://chicagocoffee.io">
              <img src="/images/2026/chicago_coffee_icon.png" alt="Chicago Coffee Map" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm" style="max-width: 150px;" />
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-10">
            <h4>Chicago Coffee Map</h4>
            <p>A React Native app for discovering specialty coffee shops across Chicago. Independent roasters and third-wave cafes with chains filtered out so you're only seeing places worth the trip. It pulls live data from Google Places and uses AI-generated summaries to give a real sense of each shop before you head out.</p>
            <p>Built on the same codebase as the Minnesota and NYC variants. Part of a growing series of city-specific coffee maps for people who take their coffee seriously.</p>
            <a href="https://chicagocoffee.io" class="btn btn-outline-primary">View Project →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr class="my-4" />

        <div class="row align-items-center mb-4 pb-4">
          <div class="col-md-2 mb-3 mb-md-0">
            <a href="https://todaysrecordhigh.com">
              <img src="/images/2025/weather_web.png" alt="Today's Record High" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm" style="max-width: 150px;" />
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-10">
            <h4>Today's Record High</h4>
            <p>A data visualization tool showcasing record high temperatures across U.S. cities. Built with .NET Core and HighCharts.</p>
            <a href="https://todaysrecordhigh.com" class="btn btn-outline-primary">View Project →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr class="my-4" />

        <div class="row align-items-center mb-4 pb-4">
          <div class="col-md-2 mb-3 mb-md-0">
            <a href="https://mncoffeemap.com">
              <img src="/images/2025/mpls_coffee.png" alt="MN Coffee Map" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm" style="max-width: 150px;" />
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-10">
            <h4>MN Coffee Map</h4>
            <p>A React Native app built to help people discover specialty coffee shops across Minnesota. Not chains, but the independent roasters and third-wave cafes worth going out of your way for. It pulls live data from Google Places, filters out the Starbucks and Caribous and surfaces AI-generated summaries so you get a real sense of a shop before making the trip.</p>
            <p>The app also integrates with Work From MSP, a local guide that scores cafes on real workday usability: Wi-Fi, outlets and noise levels for people who need somewhere better than their kitchen table. Built with React Native and Expo.</p>
            <a href="https://mncoffeemap.com" class="btn btn-outline-primary">View Project →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr class="my-4" />

